						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in front of the Dōṇikkavva temple.</p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa, 1226-27 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription states that the Sibāra, i.e., pillar, which was not in existence for the past 770 years, was erected by Maḍavari Basavayya in the cyclic year Vyaya, the 16th year after Simhaṇa entered the country. The cyclic year Vyaya in Simhaṇa's reign corresponded to 1226-27 A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
